{
  "title": "ISic001175. Halaesa honours Diogenes Lapiron, son of Diogenes ",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"θεοῖς\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">[θ]ε̣οῖς</span>  <span data-text=\"πᾶσι\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">πᾶσι</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"ὁ\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">[ὁ]</span>  <span data-text=\"δᾶμος\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"\">δᾶμος</span>  <span data-text=\"τῶν\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">τῶν</span>  <span data-text=\"Ἀλαισίνων\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"\">Ἀλαισίνων</span>  <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογένην Διογένεος\n                    Λαπίρωνα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διογένην\"><span data-text=\"Διογένην\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">[Δι]ογένην</span></span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογένεος\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Διογένεος\"><span data-text=\"Διογένεος\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"\">Διογένεος</span></span></span>  <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Λαπίρωνα\"><span data-text=\"Λαπίρωνα\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"\">Λαπίρωνα</span></span></span>  <br id=\"al5-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-text=\"εὐεργεσίας\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"\">[εὐ]εργεσίας</span>  <span data-text=\"ἕνεκεν\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"\">ἕνεκεν</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"θεοῖς\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">[.].ΟΙΣ</span><span data-text=\"πᾶσι\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">ΠΑΣΙ</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"ὁ\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">[.]</span><span data-text=\"δᾶμος\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"\">ΔΑΜΟΣ</span><span data-text=\"τῶν\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΩΝ</span><span data-text=\"Ἀλαισίνων\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"\">ΑΛΑΙΣΙΝΩΝ</span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογένην Διογένεος\n                    Λαπίρωνα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διογένην\"><span data-text=\"Διογένην\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">[..]ΟΓΕΝΗΝ</span></span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογένεος\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Διογένεος\"><span data-text=\"Διογένεος\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"\">ΔΙΟΓΕΝΕΟΣ</span></span></span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Λαπίρωνα\"><span data-text=\"Λαπίρωνα\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"\">ΛΑΠΙΡΩΝΑ</span></span></span><br id=\"al5-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-text=\"εὐεργεσίας\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"\">[..]ΕΡΓΕΣΙΑΣ</span><span data-text=\"ἕνεκεν\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"\">ΕΝΕΚΕΝ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001175_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001175_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001175.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001175-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic001175_leftthreequarter_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001175_leftthreequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001175_leftthreequarter.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001175_leftthreequarter-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text of Prag from autopsy</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>The people of the Halaesini (dedicate) to all the gods (a statue of) Diogenes Lapiron son of Diogenes on account of his beneficence.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">Maria Egizia Felice</p>  <p>Il popolo degli alesini (dedica) agli dei tutti (una statua di) Diogene Lapiro figlio di Diogene per la sua beneficenza.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The inscription has the form of a standard honorific dedication for an individual, and there are several similar texts from the area of the agora at Halaesa. Several other individuals are known from Halaesa with the second name ‘Lapiron’ (in three other inscriptions, <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001176\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001176</a>, <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000800\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000800</a>, <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003571\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003571</a> and from Cicero, In Verrem 2.2.19-28), and the name Diogenes is recorded a second time in the same family in <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001176\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001176</a> - in theory this could be the same individual (see Facella 2006: 229-241 on the family). The name Lapiron is otherwise only attested at Locri (<a href=\"http://dx.doi.org/10.1163/1874-6772_seg_a32_1018\" target=\"_blank\">SEG 32.1018</a>), although the phenomenon of such second names is common in Hellenistic Sicily (O. Masson, Onomastica Graeca Selecta (2000), vol. 2, 379-86). This block is most likely to be the base, or part of the base, for a statue or some other object dedicated to ‘all the gods’ in honour of Diogenes.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Gualtherus 1624 138 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388</a>  </li><li> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/310971\" target=\"_blank\">298</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931</a>  </li><li> Muratori 1740 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/Muratori1740Vol2\" target=\"_blank\">554 no.3</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001395\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001395</a>  </li><li> Castelli 1753 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/280755\" target=\"_blank\">143-145 no.1</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002086\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002086</a>  </li><li> Castelli 1769 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/Castelli1769\" target=\"_blank\">cl.5 no.14</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084</a>  </li><li> Castelli 1784 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/Castelli1784\" target=\"_blank\">cl.5 no.17</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083</a>  </li><li> Franz 1853 5595 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250</a>  </li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">353</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Hoffmann 1904 5201 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817</a>  </li><li> Manni Piraino 1973 127 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531</a>  </li><li> Prestianni Giallombardo 1993 tav.1 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001659\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001659</a>  </li><li> Facella 2006 230 n.30 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002013\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002013</a>  </li><li> Prestianni Giallombardo 2012 178 fig.157 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001357\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001357</a>  </li><li> Prag and Tigano 2017 no.42 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>The letters are plainly and evenly cut, and well spaced, without serifs. Epsilon has a short middle bar, omicron is full size, omega is open.</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ tyoe3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type1.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type1.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.4.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.4</a> </p> Lines 1-5  25-30  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not measured  </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
